                            <comment id="17438492" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 4 Nov 2021 05:45:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The greedy is not the problem, its because you set that exchange property at the end of the route which gets set on another thread than the consumer thread. And this is due when using EIPs in parallel mode.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="17438499" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 4 Nov 2021 05:54:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In such use-cases you need to run the scheduler in synchronous mode, eg&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;                from(&quot;scheduler:testBug?initialDelay=1000&amp;amp;useFixedDelay=true&amp;amp;delay=60000&amp;amp;greedy=true&amp;amp;synchronous=true&quot;)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17438748" author="jeremyross" created="Thu, 4 Nov 2021 14:25:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;How odd. I looked for the synchronous option the other day (I use it on timer also) and couldn&apos;t find it for some reason. My bad!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
